A former Scots rugby player who later coached Glasgow High School FP has died aged 83. Ex-Scottish rugby player dies, aged 83 A former Scots rugby player who later coached Glasgow High School FP has died aged 83.Jimmy Docherty, a stand-off with the Glasgow side, played for Scotland eight times &shy;between 1955 and 1958.His finest hour in a Scotland jersey was in 1955 when a Welsh team was defeated 14-8 - Scotland's first victory in four years. Docherty contributed a drop-goal to the success.When he retired from playing he was involved as a coach and trainer at Glasgow High School FP and was the club's president in 1980-81. 